:true,"entry_ids":["n6723","n6728"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hollow, cavity, depression"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interior, inner","examples":[{"text":"فاغرة (var. فاكرة).\nالماهية: حب يشبه الحمص له حب كالمحلب وفي جوفه حب أسود كالشهدانج يحمل من السفالة.\nالطبع: حارة يابسة في الثالثة.\nالخواص: فيها تحليل وقبض.\nأعضاء الغذاء: يدخل في الأدوية المصلحة للمعدة والكبد الباردتين وينفع من سوء الاستمراء البارد.\nأعضاء النفض: ينفع من الإسهال البارد ويعقل البطن.","english":"Sichuan pepper:\nIts essence: The fruit resembles chickpeas, it has fruits like mahaleb cherry, and in its inner there is a black fruit like hempseed, born from below.\nIts nature: Hot and dry in the third degree.\nIts peculiarities: In it there is discharging and constipation.\nAlimentary organs: It is put into drugs by reason of availing the stomach and the liver when they are cold and it is useful against calamities of cold appetite.\nExcretory organs: It helps against cold diarrhoea and constricts the belly."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"belly, abdomen"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"north","tags":["al-Andalus"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَافَ (jāfa, “to be hollow; to reach the interior of”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hollow out"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be hollow, to be concave"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَوِفَ (jawifa) (form I); hollowness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَوِفَ (jawifa) (form I); amplitude"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of أَجْوَف (ʔajwaf)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ج و ف (j w f). The sense “inner” suggests a relation with Egyptian jwf (“flesh”) since the flesh is in the “inner” part of the body. Compare Hebrew גוף (guf, “body”)."},"ipa":null}